        <div id="dsq-comment-body-68" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-68" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Just used CM-Updater installed on my G1-Dream to update from v4.0.2 to v.4.0.3.1.  It downloaded v4.0.3.1 and I allowed it to installed.  </p>
<p>It rebooted to ANDROID SYSTEM RECOVERY screen.  As a newb, I kept selecting &#8220;APPLY SD CARD. UPDATE.ZIP&#8221;, which didn&#8217;t work &amp; I should have just selected &#8220;REBOOT SYSTEM NOW&#8221;(first option).   Now all newbs will know just select REBOOT SYSTEM NOW(first option).  </p>
<p>NOTE:  First boot after updates takes a while, so expect to see ANDROID splash screen longer than usual (don&#8217;t panic).  </p>
<p>I didn&#8217;t lose any shortcuts or apps after installing v4.0.3.1.  You rock Cyan!!!!!!!</p>
